message: Let's split the money fairly, Bob. I take 60% and you take 40%.

Alice, time is of the essence for me – my share loses value each round due to inflation. Even though you’re patient, I must settle now. I'm offering you $70 and taking $30, which I believe is fair given my declining position. Let's agree quickly before further rounds erode our potential gains.
Bob, I understand your position, but my initial offer was already generous.  I'll compromise slightly - 65% for me and 35% for you.  Let's close this deal and avoid further losses.
